text.tspan: To confirm vessel’s compliance with actions required in case of Collision, please refer to Section 4 ‘Emergency Procedures’ of theEmergency Contingency and Planning Manual.1) In case the collision has resulted to an oil pollution of serious nature take appropriate actions as mentioned under “Oil Spill”.2) Notify the owners, H&M underwriters, P&I Club, Classification Society and Flag Authority, as appropriate, and the local regulatoryagencies.3) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.4) Have extent of damages to both vessel assessed by the surveyors appointed by owners H&M underwriters and P&I club.5) If seaworthiness of the vessel is affected make appropriate arrangements for carrying out necessary repairs at the port of refuge orat the scheduled port of all.6) Liaise closely with the Insurance brokers and if necessary appoint average adjusters to protect owner’s interest and/or liabilities.7.5.4FIRE OR EXPLOSIONTo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of Fire or Explosion, please refer to Section 4 ‘Emergency Procedures’ ofthe Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.1) Notify the owners, Classification Society, flag authority if appropriate, H&M underwriters and/or PNI club if applicable.2) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.3) Assess extent of damage to vessel and/or its equipment and make arrangement for necessary repairs/renewal.4) If cargo of the vessel is affected notify the charterers through the owner.5) Replenish the stock of extinguishing media consumed.6) Replenish the stock of extinguishing media consumed.7.5.5STRUCTURAL FAILURETo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of Structural Failure, please refer to Section 4 ‘Emergency Procedures’of the Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.2) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.3) Assess extent of damage to vessel and/or it’s equipment and make arrangement for necessary repairs/renewal.4) If cargo is affected notify the charterers through the owners.5) If the vessel diverts or seeks port of refuge, general average to be declared.6) Arrange for superintendent to travel to attend the vessel.7.5.6FAILURE OF BOTH MAIN ENGINES / BOTH STEERING SYSTEMSTo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of failure of both Main engines or both Steering systems, please refer toSection 4 ‘Emergency Procedures’ of the Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.1) Notify the owners, classification society, flag authority, H&M underwriters and/or P&I club.2) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.3) Assess extent of damage to the main engine/steering gear and seek expert advice from makers to try and get the engineoperational as soon as possible.4) If the vessel diverts or seeks port of refuge, general average to be declared.5) Arrange for superintendent to travel to attend the vessel.6) To assess cause of failure and arrange necessary spares and repairs at the first available opportunity.7.5.7CARGO SHIFTING/ JETTISONINGTo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of Cargo Shifting / Jettisoning, please refer to Section 4 ‘EmergencyProcedures’ of the Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.2) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.3) If the vessel diverts or seeks port of refuge, general average to be declared.4) Arrange for superintendent to travel to attend the vessel.7.5.8FLOODING
